72e95&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "https://gray-ksfy-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/NCQDXQPNEBHZNAOTB3D6N54U2I.jpg?auth=61a7a7ea3a6cb5b30488e37f685006e16a62bd9f386c75f588a7ecd1e4f9986d&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "https://gray-ksfy-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/TOZXPKFO7FDGDP3QQSG6WN2ASA.jpg?auth=80818553545612e9bd3513ca87827756936b49a08d02f9c2e1911e83f19cf385&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "https://gray-ksfy-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/BI5F6ADNGBD4LBBWF2RKQ5DY2E.jpg?auth=df0afd0a9c86ea092af3512b9f764fde7da2c3c4fefff2a869d5335d6e83d6d0&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "https://gray-ksfy-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/ER2OV6ARIVDM7ITAUYCSZ5YVCU.bmp?auth=36511a2153b71aedfbbdf0df1ccdeb053e77da2a67d931854e1700fe7c598cc2&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "https://gray-ksfy-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/PIDSBFOO6BAC3O2OB6CMQJDDNY.bmp?auth=6d170908f3db9886c095506e7d68edea7fadf75b256a1f71bcd3eecdbf3945c4&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "https://gray-ksfy-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/XM42GJL33JCL7FDPTABKE5BOZA.jpg?auth=0eb2ece0f36f65bd493724f9e00e351ff7945f2394970af7abc53afc664656bc&width=800&height=450&smart=true"], "publication-date": "2024-08-21", "text": "SIOUX FALLS, S.D. (Dakota News Now) - Special Olympics South Dakota will host their annual Heroes Pull in Sioux Falls on August 25.\n\nTeams of up to 10 will get the chance to pull a Sioux Falls firetruck and a SWAT BearCat.\n\nTeams will compete to see who can pull the firetruck 40 feet in the fastest amount of time.\n\nFor teams that cannot fill all 10 roster spots, Special Olympic athletes will be on standby to help.\n\nThe event will take place from 4 to 6 p.m. at the Unify Center.\n\nOrganizer Nancy Lehner and Special Olympic athletes Derek Smith and Lydia Van Stedum stopped by Dakota News Now to share more about the event.\n\nView more details on the Heroes Pullhere.\n\nCopyright 2024 Dakota News Now. All rights reserved.", "title": "Special Olympics to host Heroes Pull on Sunday", "top-image": "https://gray-ksfy-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/B4ZMFXUKJ5DMPF5KSDRWJLY3YA.jpg?auth=9e9c1f1b9afc6b0baaf9c07a42fd006d52a0adb1d7ed70cd84354222e0efeb56&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "domain": "www.dakotanewsnow.com", "lang": "en", "author": "", "description": "Teams of up to 10 will get the chance to pull a Sioux Falls firetruck and a Minnehaha County Sheriff’s Department SWAT BearCat.", "keywords": "Sioux Falls,South Dakota,Special Olympics,Heroes Pull,Minnehaha County Sheriff's Department,Sioux Falls Fire,firetruck,SWAT BearCat,Lydia Van Stedum,Nancy Lehner,Derek Smith"}